    "transcript_preview": "# 255_t_763_r1b_transcripts - Page 1\n\nTAPE No. T-00763(R1b)\n\n\"P.A.O. RELEASE COMMENTARY OF THE GT-7/6 FLIGHT.\"\n\nP.A.O. SINCE THEN WE HAVE DUBBED THE TAPE OFF. THE MASTER TAPE HERE IN THE CONTRO CENTER AND WE ARE NOW PREPARED TO PLAY IT FOR YOU - IT CONTAINS REFERENCES TO SIGHTING NOT ONLY SOME PARTICLES BUT AS WELL AS AN UNIDENTIFIED OBJECT PLUS THE BOOSTER HERS THAT TAPE WE'LL PLAY IT FOR YOU NOW----\n\nS/C GEMINI-7 HERE HOUSTON-- HOW DO YOU READ?\nHOUSTON: LOUD AND CLEAR SEVEN - GO AHEAD.\nS/C (BORMAN) A BOGEY AT TEN O'CLOCK HIGH.\nHOUSTON THIS IS HOUSTON, SAY AGAIN SEVEN?\nS/C (BORMAN) I SAID WE HAVE A BOGEY AT TEN O'CLOCK HIGH.\nHOUSTON ROGER. GEMINI-7 ISTHAT THE BOOSTER OR IS THAT A NATURAL SIGHTING?\nS/C A WHAT?\nHOUSTON SAY AGAIN SEVEN.\nS/C (BORMAN) WE HAVE DEBRIS UP HERE - THIS IS AN ACTUAL SIGHTING.\nHOUSTON YOU HAVE ANY MORE INFORMATION - ESTIMATE DISTANCE OR SIZE?\nS/C (BORMAN) WE ALSO HAVE THE BOOSTER IN SIGHT.\nHOUSTON UNDERSTAND YOU ALSO HAVE THE BOOSTER IN SIGHT. ROGER.\nS/C (BORMAN) WE HAVE VERY, VERY MANY A - IT LOOKS LIKE HUNDREDS OF LITTLE PARTICLES GOING BY TO THE LEFT OUT ABOUT THREE OR FOUR MILES.\nHOUSTON UNDERSTAND YOU HAVE MANY SMALL PARTICLES GOING BY ON THE LEFT AT WHAT DISTANCE?\nS/C (BORMAN) ....GARBLED ... FOUR MILES. OH, ABOUT - GARBLED - IT LOOKS LIKE A PATH OF THE VEHICLE AT 90 DEGREES.\nHOUSTON ROGER. UNDERSTAND THEY'RE ABOUT THREE OR FOUR MILES AWAY\nS/C (BORMAN) THEY'VE PASSED NOW. THEY'RE GOING INTO POLAR ORBIT.\nHOUSTON ROGER. UNDERSTAND THEY WERE THREE TO FOUR MILES AWAY.\nS/C THATS WHAT IT APPEARED LIKE. THATS ROGER.\nHOUSTON GEMINI-7 - HOUSTON - WERE THESE PARTICLES IN ADDITION TO THE BOOSTER AND THE BOGEY AT TEN O'CLOCK HIGH?\nS/C (LOVELL) ROGER. I HAVE THE BOOSTER ON MY SIDE. ITS A BRILLIANT BODY IN THE SUN AGAINST A BLACK BACKGROUND WITH TRILLIONS OF PARTICLES ON IT.\nHOUSTON ROGER WHAT DIRECTION IS IT FROM YOU?\nS/C (LOVELL) ITS ABOUT AT MY TWO O'CLOCK POSITION.\nHOUSTON DOES THAT MEAN ITS AHEAD OF YOU?\nS/C (LOVELL) ITS AHEAD OF US AT TWO O'CLOCK, SLOWLY TUMBLING\nHOUSTON ROGER.\n.......... LONG PAUSE......... DUAL TRANSMISSION........\nP.A.O. THIS IS GEMINI CONTROL AGAIN THE REFERENCE IN THAT CONVERSATION TO THE THIRD AND UNIDENTIFIED OBJECT OF COURSE WAS OR THE THIRD OBJECT WAS A [redacted] BOGEY. THERE WERE SEVERAL REFERENCES TO THE BOGEY. AT 4 Hrs 24 MIN INTO THE FLIGHT THIS IS GEMINI CONTROL.\n\n- 1 -\n\n--- Page Break ---\n\n# 255_t_763_r1b_transcripts - Page 2\n\nT-00763 (R1B)\n\n\"UFO SIGHTING BY BORMAN\" (GT-7)\n\nSince then we have dubbed the tape off\nthe master tape here in the Control Center and we\nare now prepared to play it for you. It contains\nreferences to sighting not only some particles but\nas well as an unidentified object and plus the booster\nhere is that tape we'll play it for you now -\n\nS/C :- Gemini 7 here Houston - how do you read?\nHouston :- loud & clear 7 go ahead.\nS/C :- a bogey at 10 o'clock high (Borman)\nHouston :- this is Houston say again seven?\nS/C :- Borman I said we have a bogey at 10 o'clock high.\nHouston :- Roger. Gemini 7 is that the booster or is that\na natural sighting?\nS/C :- a what?\nHouston :- Say again seven.\nS/C :- Borman we have debris up here - this is an actual sighting\nHouston :- you have anymore information? Estimate\ndistance or size?\nS/C :- Borman We also have the booster in sight.\nHouston :- Understand you also have the booster in sight. roger,\nS/C :- Borman We have [redacted] [redacted] a it looks like hundreds of\na going little a particles going by to the left out about\n3 to 4 miles\nHouston :- understand you have many small particles going\n\n--- Page Break ---\n\n# 255_t_763_r1b_transcripts - Page 3\n\nHouston:\nbogey on the left at what distance?\n\nS/C:- Bowman\n- garbled - 4 miles. It looks like a [crossed out: round] vehicle [crossed out: faulty] painted on about - garbled -\nit looks like a path of the vehicle at 90 degrees\nHouston:- Roger. understand they're about 3 to 4 miles away\nS/C:- Bowman they passed now - they're going into polar orbit\nHouston:- Roger understand they were 3-4 miles away.\nS/C:- that's what it appeared like. that's roger.\nHouston:- Gemini-7- Houston - were these particles in\naddition to the booster and the bogey at 10 o'clock high\n[crossed out text]\n\nS/C:- (Lovell):- Roger. I have the booster myself\nit's a brilliant body in the sun against a black\nbackground with millions of particles on it.\nHouston:- roger what direction is it from you.\nS/C:- (Lovell) it's about at my 2 o'clock position.\nHouston:- does that mean that it's ahead of you?\nS/C:- (Lovell) it's ahead of us at 2 o'clock slowly [crossed out: tumbling]\nHouston- roger.\n[long pause - two garbled transmissions] tumbling\n[crossed out: Gemini Control] PAO: Gemini Control here again the reference\nin that conversation to the third and unidentified\nobject of course - was [arrow pointing to 'the'] the third object was\na bogey\n\n--- Page Break ---\n\n# 255_t_763_r1b_transcripts - Page 4\n\nPAO! - there were several references to the bogey\nthis is the unidentified object in addition to\nthe particles which appeared to be headed in a\npolar orbit you heard Frank Borman\nsay plus Jim Lovell describe discussing\nthe booster it was Borman who reported\nsighting the bogey - this is Gemini Control in\nHouston at [illegible] 24 min into the flight.\n\ntime:- 05 min: 34 sec."
